What shocking submission. I‚Äôve never seen one of these work before but there you go. 

The first forearm choke in ufc history performed by @alexandr_romanov_comrat. He improves to 13-0.

What a headkick by @adrianyanez93. A first round finish and this is surely a bonus. 

This guy is a real problem at 155, his striking is incredible.
So close to a perfect KO. What a wheel kick by Pettis. Showtime by name, showtime by nature. @showtimepettis
What a brutal knockout from @gervontaa. A reminder of how good he is in case you‚Äôve forgotten.
We live for the iconic moments, this was iconic as it gets @blessedmma
A huge win for @bambamtuivasa. Unfortunately no shoey, the commission stopped him but huge 1st round KO for BamBam.

The first fight of the night ends in a KO. A nice 3rd round knockout for @mileschapojohns. Attacking fighters whilst looking to break is very underrated, something @robinblackmartialarts talks about a lot. DC did this to Miocic to claim th heavyweight title back in 2018. 

Johns improves to 11-1 (2-1 in the UFC)

First fight of the night, first submission of the night for @joelelfenomenoalvarez. A first round submission off his back and he improves to 18-2 (3-1) unfortunately won‚Äôt get a bonus for this as he missed weight.

Great win for @thehanyakdj. The Leg kicks hurt him, the punches finished him üí•

A great comeback story, Jacoby made his ufc debut aged 23, 9 years ago. He went 0-2 before being released by the organisation. In august he made his zuffa comeback at DWTNCS and followed up with this as his UFC comeback a 1st round Knockout. Great job Dustin. üëç

A ufc debut and @shavkatrakhmonov94 improves to 13-0 (13 finishes) with a first round finish against a 19 fight veteran in cowboy Oliveira who was himself on a 3 fight win a streak. 

Very impressive and this kid will be a handful moving forward.
What is in the water over there in Dagestan? @nurmagomedov_said with a beautiful 51 second knockout. He improves to 14-2 (3-1) in the ufc.
Who says you can‚Äôt knock someone down or knock someone out with a jab? No one told  Tom Breese #ufc

Some fighters give themselves nicknames, others are give one @koreanzombiemma is the latter. 

A relentless striker with outstanding BJJ, Korean Zombie is so close to another shot at the title and a win this weekend will make him the clear #1 contender.

Just in case you‚Äôve forgotten how special @briantcity is, here is a reminder. It‚Äôs been 22 months so you can be forgiven for forgetting but never disregard his talent again after watching this.

He will finally settle the score with @koreanzombiemma next weekend.
This is one of the best knockouts I‚Äôve ever seen. Take a bow @newmansa94. If you missed it, here it is, one of the greatest knockouts of all time in MMA.

This fight between @charlesjourdain1 and @joshculibao had everything. A huge underdog overcoming the odds, a knockdown, close submission attempts, a self inflicted eye pokes, groin shots, bad refing and bad judging. You couldn‚Äôt make this stuff up, the only thing missing was a winner Nonetheless a very entertaining split decision draw. 

Note: how on a judge gave jourdain 30-27 (barring in mind that he was knocked down and almost finished in rd 1) is beyond me.

I wish I was a fly on the wall for this one. Two of the greatest Brazilian UFC fighters of all time @rdosanjosmma and @josealdojunioroficial sparring. Reminds me of the old Chute Boxe Academy stories we would hear about legendary sparring sessions.
It took 72 seconds for @luigivendramini.ufc to dispatch Jesse Ayari. Great start to the fight card. Solid left took counter and swarmed on him for the win
Unfortunately missed weight so won‚Äôt get a bonus for this one but what a performance by @lajosko.klein in his ufc debut. A first round KO of Shane Young. #ufc253
Accurate @khamzat_chimaev.

When you begin learning martial arts, you‚Äôll be lucky to learn from the best coaches around but imagine learning how to kick from one of the MMA GOATs @spiderandersonsilva. A short clip from @simeonpanda‚Äôs time at Silva‚Äôs gym.

In order to improve at any discipline as a martial artist, you should seek knowledge from the best in that discipline. 

@josealdojunioroficial is known for his quick hands and thunderous leg kicks and a few years back he trained with @teammikeygarcia to sharpen his boxing skills. 

Here is a short clip of Aldo sparring with Garcia back in 2017

üì∑: @elieseckbach

The narrative going into this weekends fight between @stylebender and @borrachinhamma is that Costa has catch Izzy as this will be a standing war. 

However let‚Äôs not forget that Costa is an extremely powerful grappler. When he entered TUF he was known more as grappler. If this fight hits the ground, his black belt may well be the deciding factor in this fight.

Iron sharpens Iron. 145lb champ @alexvolkanovski sparring 135lb champ @petr_yan at @tigermuaythai. Both champions have gone out to train with the team since 2014 and their high level striking game came be attributed to the time the spend in Thailand. #ufc
Huge underdog @minner135. Get the submission in under a minute. Guillotine master gets the guillotine again.

If you set gimmicks, trash talking and politics aside, you‚Äôll realise that @colbycovmma is very special fighter. 

Here is an old clip of him wrestling with former teammate Jorge Masvidal. (How times have changed right?) 

Colby is often discredited or routed against due to his antics outside of the cage. But on closer inspection, his volume striking, relentless takedowns and insane cardio make him a nightmare for pretty much anyone.

There has been a narrative going into the @twooodley and @colbycovmma that Tyron needs to get back to ‚Äúthe old Tyron Woodley‚Äù and ‚Äúlet his hands go‚Äù in order to win. So I‚Äôve made a little breakdown to explain why (in my opinion) this narrative isn‚Äôt true. 

If you‚Äôve watched a lot of footage on both fighters, you‚Äôll have a rough idea of how this fight will play out. (Hint: Woodley by KO/TKO or Covington 50-45)

The return of @anthony_rumble to the 205lbs division could not be timed any better. With the future of the division up in the air, I feel bad for the person tasked with welcoming Rumble back into the division.

There is often a discussion about which boxer would transition best to MMA. In my opinion, @lomachenkovasiliy should be the clear choice. A master of combination punches and finding angles, Loma is not only a nightmare to defend against but his footwork make him nearly impossible to hit clean. Having practiced wrestling in his youth, a few months of refining his takedown defence, give him those 4oz gloves and he‚Äôll be a nightmare for the UFC 135lbs division. 
.
His achievements in boxing are stunning. A 396-1 record as an amateur (with his only loss being avenged twice). 2 gold medals at the olympics in 2008 and 2012. Loma has a pro record of 14-1 (the 1 loss being extremely controversial for repeated low blows). Loma became the fastest pro to obtain titles in 3 weight classes with this knockout. 
.
As he sits at top of the current pound-for-pound list, this MMA fan can only dream of Loma one day deciding to give MMA a shot.

The calf kick is becoming more common in MMA. Traditionally fighters would throw leg kicks to the thigh, but throwing it to the calf seems to be more effective. The calf kicks seems harder to check and adrenaline doesn‚Äôt stop that particular kick from hurting. Battering the lead leg of a power or combination puncher stops them from sitting down on their punches. @rakic_ufc displayed this beautifully last night.
Perfectly timed knee by @martinez3jonathan. Missed weight so won‚Äôt be eligible for a bonus, regardless this knee was beautiful and is the first finish of the event. #knockout #ufc

For all those who think @chitoveraufc was ‚Äúlucky‚Äù watch this again carefully. Chito and O Malley both stand in the southpaw stance and Chito hits O Malley with a low calf kick to his right leg. O Malleys leg begins to buckle and lose most of its mobility and he rolls it several times before it finally gives. This is very similar to DJ vs Cejudo and Primus vs Chandler. Solid win by Chito Vera.
A short clip of @danhangman and @stylebender hard sparring before they joined the @ufc. Beautiful display of striking #mma

The rise of young @edmenshahbazyan has been nothing short of sensational. Currently ranked #9 in the stacked middleweight division, he is 11-0 with 10 first round knockouts. Edmen is back this weekend.

7 British fighters are fighting tonight, each in a different weight class. Exciting night for British MMA. Good luck to them all @darrentill2 @theprospectmma @bigpaulcraig @mike_grundy @tomaspinall93 @jai_herbert_mma and @rhysmckeemma #BritishMMA
In 2015 before he joined the UFC, a young @stylebender was bought in to train with @anthony_rumble in preparation for his fight with @jonnybones. Here is a short clip of Izzy sparring with Rumble.

After some wins and some loses for the Brits on fight island. Let‚Äôs take a look back at a Brit who was also searching for greatness before he became a ufc champion. In a division of killers ruled by a champion who had already beaten him, @mikebisping found a way to achieve his life long goal. This a short clip before his fight in London with the GOAT Anderson Silva. This clip embodies everything that Bisping stands for, hard work and desire for greatness.
Beautiful head movement by both @robwhittakermma and @darrentill2 last night‚Äôs main event #ufc
What a debut by @tomaspinall93. The future is bright for @teamkaobon. #knockout
A short clip of former UFC Champion @cody_nolove sparring rising contender Song Yadong at @teamalphamalemma. Two of the very best in the stacked 135lb division.
A little clip of @darrentill2 sparring during camp with @paulkellymma. The Gorilla returns this weekend against former champion @robwhittakermma.

The fight game is cruel, you‚Äôll win some and you‚Äôll lose some. Here is a short but beautiful clip of @karatehottiemma and @karatecutie after Waterson‚Äôs lose to Herica Tiburcio at @invictafc 10. A cruel reminder of how heartbreaking a loss can be but also a reminder of the more important things in life.

Continuing the theme of the greats from other sports, here is a video of @zhangweilimma sparring with muaythai great @saenchaithailand. Generally considered to be the all-time pound-for-pound best by most. Watching the UFC champion spar with him is a joy.

A short clip of @tjdillashaw sparring with @lomachenkovasiliy. As a MMA fighter, no matter how good you think you are at any discipline, specialist in that discipline (in this case boxing) can open your eyes to new techniques and footwork that you never understood before.

With @petr_yan impressively finishing @josealdojunioroficial. He is now the undisputed champion at 135lbs. But with a huge list of contenders, this is probably the most stacked this division has ever been. With 5 former champions including @tjdillashaw, @dominickcruz, @cody_nolove, @josealdojunioroficial and @frankieedgar (6 if you include @henry_cejudo) all lurking in the wings. The list of contenders and rising stars including @mmarlonmoraes, @funkmastermma, @sugaseanmma, @pedromunhozmma, @enterthesandman135 and yadongsong are also lining up for their chance at UFC gold. This is possibly the most stacked division in ufc history. Who do you want to be champion at the end of 2021?
After a disappointing start to his ufc career, the run @lukerockhold went on to earn his title was nothing short of legendary. Here is a compilation of all of Rockhold‚Äôs finishes in the UFC.

The relationship between @kgastelum and @kingsmma_hb is something to behold. The improvements that Gastelum has made since joining King‚Äôs MMA is nothing short of extraordinary. After a few bumps on their mission for gold, they resume their journey against Jack Hermansson on UFC Fight Island tomorrow night.

A nice clip from 5 years ago, Before @dc_mma fought Rumble Johnson for the Vacant title. @khabib_nurmagomedov tells DC that he had to be more humble as he was being told off by his father Abdulmanap Nurmagomedov. This shows the influence that Abdulmanap had on Khabib‚Äôs career that he immediately had to humble himself in his fathers presence. RIP to the great Abdulmanap Nurmagomedov

Speed, Power and Determination. The Scouse-nese Gorilla @darrentill2 returns against the former middleweight champion Robert Whittaker next week on UFC Fight Island. Here is a compilation of all his knockdowns in the UFC
UFC 251‚Äôs main event mere SECONDS away from getting CANCELLED. These guys are on sight, but they missed each other by seconds. @gamebredfighter @usman84kg
